	</p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 regular session</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">Senate Bill 534</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Senator Deeds</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced January 20, 2026; referred <br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;to the Committee on the Judiciary; and then to the Committee on Finance]	</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL </span><a name="_Hlk219365873"><span class="csEF05ACC">to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding a new article, designated &sect;60-11-1, &sect;60-11-2, &sect;60-11-3, &sect;60-11-3a, &sect;60-11-4, &sect;60-11-5, &sect;60-11-6, &sect;60-11-7, &sect;60-11-8, &sect;60-11-9, &sect;60-11-10, &sect;60-11-11, and &sect;60-11-12; and to repeal &sect;19-12F-1, &sect;19-12F-2, &sect;19-12F-3, &sect;19-12F-4, &sect;19-12F-5, &sect;19-12F-6, &sect;19-12F-7, &sect;19-12F-8, &sect;19-12F-9, &sect;19-12F-10, &sect;19-12F-11, &sect;60-10-1, and &sect;60-10-2, relating to the West Virginia Kratom Consumer Protection Act; providing a short title and findings; defining terms; regulating and permitting the sale of kratom; prohibiting certain practices; giving rule-making authority; requiring age verification; taxing kratom business; creating an application process; permitting cooperative enforcement agreements; permitting seizure of contraband; creating criminal penalties; establishing a licensing fund; and permitting coordination. </span></a></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><h1 class="cs709C557D">
		<span class="csE70BDF83">CHAPTER 19. AGRICULTURE.</span></h1>
	<h2 class="cs89687900">
